!curse.description: What curse? You're just the fucking best.
Good thing there's a !food command, huh?
Get more, and keep what's yours.
Time for a break.
What makes [i]them[/i] so great!?
GOD FUCKING DAMNIT!
C'mon. You knew this one was in here somewhere. ♥
You can't turn down a game of chance or a bet. Just one or two more games couldn't hurt...
A raincloud follows you everywhere, pouring on your head.
Oh yeah, this curse is soooooooo great. You just LOVE it.
Can't stop moving, even if you want to.
You can only speak in rhyme, though the rhyme scheme is up to you. Couplets, limericks, anything!
Every 15 minutes, you forget what just happ- wait, why am I here again?
You speak your mind about anything and everything you're thinking.
The more they look at you, the hornier you get.
Be careful to not trip on that branch, or drop whatever you're holding...
Everything metallic sticks to you. Stay away from electronics.
You are overcome by an intense fear chosen by the person invoking this curse.
A mysterious voice narrates your movements and thoughts to all those around you.
Everyone seems to be hiding something from you. Just what are they scheming...?
Whenever someone says your name, you both are flung 10 feet into the air like ragdolls.
Everything you try to do just barely doesn't work for some reason!
You refer to yourself only in the third person, usually with your name.
Red light lasting too long? Shopping cart in the middle of the aisle? There's always SOMETHING.
You have sloooooooooowed down. The world seems to move faster than you can manage!
You meant to lie to someone, but instead you ended up choosing to lie on the floor.
Your name is Chungus. No one else remembers any differently, and you can't tell them otherwise.
A ghost follows you around, clapping two halves of a coconut like a horse whenever you move.
You mishear and misread words often as something much more risque.
Your hands and arms automatically act out your subconscious desires, no matter what they may be.
Life is hard when you randomly pass out for a quick nap in the middle of something important.
Did you mean to smash your cup? Sometimes, you just don't know your own strength!
Any time you hear a pun, you must reply with a pun of your own.
You become obsessed with undermining the next person to slight you. No matter how trivial it was.
Youwu can owonly tawk in uwu cyutsie tawk uwu
Anything fluid that goes into your mouth just dribbles down your chin, but it usually doesn't even make it INTO your mouth.
Every 30 minutes or so, you are overcome with the desire to advertise a product.
You keep stepping on Lego bricks whenever you walk. It happens at random, but no less frequently than every 20 steps.
No one believes a word you say, whether you're telling the truth or not.
You can try, but it won't go in. Anywhere.
Pleasure and pain are completely flipped. Things that would normally cause pleasure hurt instead, and vice versa.

Right-handers become lefties, and vice versa, but you will still habitually try to use your previously dominant hand... with the amount of skill your non-dominant hand would have. This also applies to legs/feet.
You can only speak in song lyrics, though they can be from any song you know.
Every part of you is a different color than it started. Hair, skin, eyes, lips, feathers, stripes, tattoos, markings... everything is different.
There's an awful itch that won't go away. Whenever you try to scratch it, it just moves somewhere else on your body.
You turn into a plushie version of yourself. Soft fabric, seams, and some kind of stuffing (cotton, fiberfill, foam bits, beanie-baby style balls). You can still move around and feel everything.
At least one of your limbs is asleep at all times, though it may be at different stages. Numbness, pins and needles, stiffness, cramping...
Whatever can go wrong will go wrong, at least as far as your clothing is concerned. Accidental exposure is practically inevitable (unless you're already nude of course).
